      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:29:10",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ قَذَفَ امْرَأَتَهُ فَتَلَاعَنَا ثُمَّ قَذَفَهَا بَعْدَ مَا تَفَرَّقَا أَيْضاً بِالزِّنَى أَ عَلَيْهِ حَدٌّ قَالَ نَعَمْ عَلَيْهِ حَدٌّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn, from Safwan, from Shuayb, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about a man who accused his wife, so he cursed, then accused her after the separation as well, with the adultery, is there a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) upon him?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Yes, upon him is the Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>)’."
        ]
      }
    },
